whats all this for 
Lite
The code you're seeing is the Visual Mirror Editor I designed for you. It's the "Pro" version of your content manager that actually looks like your real website while you're editing it.
Here is exactly what each part of that code does for you:
1. The "Visual Mirror" (The CSS at the top)
The @import and the .v-hero, .v-title, etc., are there to copy the exact design of your Home page. This is what makes the editor "mirror" the real site. Instead of looking at a boring admin form, you see your actual website layout inside the manager.
2. The "Live Inputs" (v-input)
Instead of standard text boxes, I used these "Live Inputs." They allow you to click directly on the text (like the title "Taste of Uganda") and type your changes. It feels like you are editing the live website.
3. The "Edit Overlays" (edit-overlay)
These create a dashed border when you hover over a section. It shows you exactly what part of the website you are about to change, making it very easy to use without making mistakes.
4. The "Change Background" Buttons
Since your Home page has big background images, I added floating buttons that appear when you hover over the Hero section or the Food cards. This lets you upload new images directly to those specific spots.
5. The "Slide Navigation"
Since your home page has a slideshow, I added the dots at the bottom of the editor so you can switch between slides and edit the content of each one individually.
In short: This code turns your admin panel from a simple "data entry form" into a Professional Visual Design Tool. You see the changes as you make them, ensuring your website always looks perfect.
